The JSP code won&#39;t compile, because you didn&#39;t import classes `Userdb` and `User` by the `@page import` directive. The syntax of this directive is similar to Java import statement. You can read more here [Using Package Members][3].

```
&lt;%@ page import=&quot;mypackage.Userdb&quot; %&gt;    
&lt;%@ page import=&quot;mypackage.User&quot; %&gt; 
```
 The second problem is in the `Userdb` class in the method `getAllUser()`. The `Connection` object should be closed at the end of the method. If you didn&#39;t close connection it will stay active and keep memory, it imposes a memory leaks (also known as resource leaks). In the java 8 and above this object implements [`AutoClosable`][1] interface and can be used with [*try-with-resources*][2] statement. The same is related to `Statement` and `ResultSet` that you should close accordingly. But if you close the connection explicitly then these objects are closed also.


```
try (Connection connection = db.getConnection();) {
  //your code here                         
}catch(SQLException e) {
  db.getErrorMessages(e);
}     
```

  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/AutoCloseable.html
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/essential/exceptions/tryResourceClose.html
  [3]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/package/usepkgs.html

