Always check if `getText()` returns null, you can use `TextUtils.isEmpty(string)` for convenience.

Also, `Integer.parseInt(string)` may throw an exception, should be handled with something like [this][1], or just show an error with a `Toast`.

```
public static int parseWithDefault(String number, int defaultVal) {
  try {
    return Integer.parseInt(number);
  } catch (NumberFormatException e) {
    return defaultVal;
